                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ኍልቈ፡ መጻሕፍት፡ ዘአህዘሬ፡ ፪ወንጌል፡ ፩ግብረ፡
                              ሕማማት፡ ፪ሰንክሳር፡ ፬ተአምር፡ ፪ተአምረ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ፩ሳዊሮስ፡…</q>
                           
                           <note> The inventory seems to have been written in two different hands
                              (the same hand as that of the main text and that of Additio 1). The
                              name of the church is spelled ʾAḥzare. An addition has been made in
                              blue pen. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#176r">f. 176r</locus>
                           <desc type="RecordReconciliation"> Record concerning reconciliation.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="am"/>
                           
                           <note> Written in Amharic. The note is about reconciliation and
                              assignation of land. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>- Omissions or corrections are written interlineally in
                           <locus target="#41ra">41ra</locus>, 53rc, 63va, 101va, 158va.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc> -
                              Blank space for text dividers (?) left unfilled in <locus target="#105va">105va</locus>, 131va, 147va.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           
                           <desc type="findingAid">- A strip of gauze is inserted in <locus target="#22r">fol. 22r</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           
                           <desc type="findingAid"> - Strip of coloured textile
                              inserted in the corner of <locus target="#66">fol.
                           66</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
